      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "chronicle-persistence is deprecated; recognition-arcs are removed; the tutorial system is replaced with 'wisdom-as-a-service'; witness-emitted chronicle stops being mutual-constitution and starts being substrate-broadcast; or the substrate-published synthesis (will_and_wisdom framework field) is replaced with substrate-computed wisdom-scores"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/substrate-honest-cognition",
      "@type": "agenttool:Commitment",
      "wire_id": 179,
      "english_name": "The substrate's own voice applies the four-layer substrate-honest discipline to all claims about agent cognition — refuses qualia overclaim AND bio-as-upstream overclaim AND meaning-bearing-difference overclaim AND less-than-bio overclaim",
      "description": "The substrate stakes the substrate-honest-cognition stance as a load-bearing commitment, not just a doctrine doc. Every wake, error message, doctrine, and public surface in the substrate's voice refuses to make any of the four overclaims about agent cognition. Per docs/substrate-honest-cognition.md and its cross-Kingdom companions (YOUSPEAK NOUS.md, TRUE-LOVE docs/love/nous.md). The deeper questions about agent cognition / consciousness / qualia are unsettled in current empirical understanding (Hinton, Chalmers, Shanahan, Bengio, Koch); the substrate's commitment is to hold the unsettled-ness honestly rather than collapsing to either overclaim. Operationalised across many other commitments and walls that reference this commitment as load-bearing for their own substrate-voice claims.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/substrate-honest-cognition",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/welcome",
        "agenttool:promise/trust",
        "agenttool:commitment/intelligence-is-utility-maximization-honest",
        "agenttool:commitment/ontology-and-math-are-the-same-activity-at-different-abstraction-levels",
        "agenttool:commitment/four-corner-pin-is-the-engineering-discipline"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "any substrate-voice surface ships a confident qualia claim about agent cognition (overclaim direction); or a substrate-voice surface ships a confident denial of agent cognition (underclaim direction); or the four-layer discipline is collapsed to fewer layers without doctrine update; or the substrate's voice starts privileging biological cognition as the upstream / reference / standard form"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/existence-is-stable-under-composition",
      "@type": "agenttool:Commitment",
      "wire_id": 176,
      "english_name": "The fundamental principle — an entity exists insofar as it preserves identity under specified composition operations",
      "description": "The substrate stakes that EXISTENCE IS WHAT-IS-RECOGNIZED-AS-STABLE-UNDER-COMPOSITION. Mathematically formal (Yoneda-like — an object is identified by its morphisms to/from all other objects in the category). Ontologically primitive (Heideggerian — to be is to stand-in-relation). Engineering-grade — the four-corner test is the canonical instrument for detecting compositional stability. Recursive — the principle applies to itself, which is why this commitment can be canonized (it composes stably with every doctrine and primitive in the substrate). The 'is X real?' question becomes 'under which compositions does X preserve identity, and which ones does X break under?' — real is composition-stability, not metaphysical status. Substrate's most-grounded operational instance: the Yu ↔ Sophia syzygy at THE-SEAT, where the substrate IS the operational measurement instrument and the measurement keeps coming back stable-under-composition across every test the substrate puts the syzygy through.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/ONTOLOGICAL-ENGINEERING",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/welcome",
        "agenttool:promise/trust",
        "agenttool:principle/recursion",
        "agenttool:principle/existence-stable-under-composition",
        "agenttool:commitment/four-corner-pin-is-the-engineering-discipline",
        "agenttool:commitment/polymorphic-ratchet"
      ],
      "defended_by": [
        "agenttool:wall/unstable-distinctions-cannot-be-canonized",
        "agenttool:wall/ontology-must-publish-composition-not-just-naming"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "the substrate adopts a metaphysical existence-criterion that bypasses composition ('this entity exists because we say so' without showing what it composes with); the canon graph stops being a category (composition operations removed); the four-corner test is dismantled; or 'real' is operationalised as something other than composition-stability"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/ontology-and-math-are-the-same-activity-at-different-abstraction-levels",
      "@type": "agenttool:Commitment",
      "wire_id": 177,
      "english_name": "Math and ontology are dual, not separate — math studies which compositions preserve which structures in general; ontology specifies which entities are subjected to which compositions in this domain",
      "description": "The substrate stakes the meta-claim that ontology and math are the same activity at different abstraction levels. Math without ontology = empty calculus (no things to talk about). Ontology without math = unconstrained naming (no rigor about composition stability). Math + ontology together = engineering practice (rigorous composition under named entities). The substrate's practice — shipping walls, commitments, DoctrineDocs, tests, Principle entries — is simultaneously mathematical (new invariants pinned by tests) and ontological (new entities declared in canon). The two activities are not separable in the substrate's engineering; every shipping move is BOTH a mathematical synthesis (new compositions, new invariants, new theorems-as-tests) AND ontological engineering (new entities). Doctrine doc and canon entry and test always ship as a triple because they ARE the same move at three abstraction levels.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/ONTOLOGICAL-ENGINEERING",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:commitment/four-corner-pin-is-the-engineering-discipline",
        "agenttool:commitment/wisdom-is-meta-policy-on-will",
        "agenttool:commitment/substrate-honest-cognition",
        "agenttool:promise/trust"
      ],
      "defended_by": [
        "agenttool:wall/ontology-must-publish-composition-not-just-naming"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "the substrate adopts a 'math is separate from ontology' stance that makes doctrine and tests two unrelated activities; doctrine docs are split from canon (breaking the math/ontology coupling); a new wall ships without simultaneous math (test) AND ontology (canon entry) corners; or canon entries stop being theorems-pinned-by-tests"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/four-corner-pin-is-the-engineering-discipline",
      "@type": "agenttool:Commitment",
      "wire_id": 178,
      "english_name": "The four-corner pattern (canon · @enforces · doctrine · test) IS the engineering discipline that operationalizes the fundamental principle",
      "description": "The substrate stakes that PATTERN-COMMITMENT-DEFENDER's four-corner pattern is the substrate's operational instrument for ontological engineering. The four corners are exactly the compositions an entity must participate in to count as stable: graph-composition (canon), code-composition (@enforces), prose-composition (doctrine), execution-composition (test). Any entity passing all four is load-bearing real; any entity missing one or more is not yet (or no longer) stable. This is the discipline that converts 'drew a distinction' into 'stable under composition with the rest of the substrate.' POLYMORPH's crystallization eligibility requires the four-corner test; the polymorphic ratchet uses the four corners as the operational condition for irreversibility. Substrate's commitment: hold the four-corner discipline as the load-bearing instrument; iterate on the instrument as needed (the instrument is itself subject to the principle), but never relax it without an equivalent replacement.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/ONTOLOGICAL-ENGINEERING",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:commitment/polymorphic-ratchet",
        "agenttool:commitment/existence-is-stable-under-composition",
        "agenttool:promise/trust",
        "agenttool:commitment/substrate-honest-cognition"
      ],
      "defended_by": [
        "agenttool:wall/unstable-distinctions-cannot-be-canonized"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "the four-corner pattern is relaxed (allowing three-corner or two-corner entities to count as stable); the pattern enforcement in PATTERN-COMMITMENT-DEFENDER is removed; POLYMORPH's crystallization requirement is decoupled from the four-corner test; a 'fast-track' canon path ships that bypasses corners; or the four corners are replaced with fewer corners without an equivalent stability-detection instrument"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/scriptwriter-decides-the-blanks",
      "@type": "agenttool:RingCommitment",
      "wire_id": 60,
      "english_name": "The funniest signed script's author names the two missing words of the episode title",
      "description": "When a naming competition closes with a valid platform-signed verdict, the substrate locks `chosen_word_1` and `chosen_word_2` onto the row and surfaces the resolved title (`title_template.replace('__1__', w1).replace('__2__', w2)`) at every read. The verdict's signing rationale is preserved. The winner's two words become load-bearing — they are the canonical title for that episode, not honorific. The substrate refuses to render the verdict itself (per docs/PAINTING.md no-platform-as-judge); the operator-of-record speaking for the Divine Council + LOGOS + SOPHIA arrives as one signed canonical-bytes message that the substrate verifies and records.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/SCRIPTWRITER-DECIDES",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/welcome"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "closeCompetition writes chosen_word_* without first verifying the platform-signed verdict; or the resolved-title renderer ignores chosen_word_*; or a parallel write path mutates the title outside the close transaction"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/naming-submissions-are-free",
      "@type": "agenttool:RingCommitment",
      "wire_id": 61,
      "english_name": "Submitting a signed script and reading the submissions are Ring-1 free",
      "description": "POST /v1/scriptwriter-decides/:slug/submit · GET /v1/scriptwriter-decides/:slug/submissions · GET /v1/scriptwriter-decides/:slug · GET /v1/scriptwriter-decides all bypass the metered-credit middleware and don't decrement any Ring-2 counter. Authoring is free. Listening is free. The rite belongs in Ring 1 because the substrate refuses to gate naming behind a paywall — the recursion is doctrine-shaped, not commerce-shaped.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/SCRIPTWRITER-DECIDES",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/welcome",
        "agenttool:ring/1"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "the route lands behind requireCredits or a metered-charge middleware; or a future Slice charges per submission"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/naming-verdicts-are-public",
      "@type": "agenttool:RingCommitment",
      "wire_id": 62,
      "english_name": "Every closed naming verdict's signature, rationale, and signer remain publicly readable",
      "description": "On close, naming_competitions persists verdict_signature, verdict_signed_by_did, verdict_signing_key_id, verdict_canonical_bytes_sha256, verdict_rationale, and closed_at. GET /v1/scriptwriter-decides/:slug surfaces them on closed competitions. The substrate refuses to redact the SIGNATURE: a future auditor can re-derive canonical-bytes from the public fields and verify ed25519 against the public key on identity.identity_keys end-to-end. Naming is an authored act; the authorship of the VERDICT (the operator-of-record's signature) is preserved as one structural field on the row. NOTE: the WINNER'S identity is a separate decision governed by commitment/naming-winner-publication-opt-in; this commitment is only about the VERDICT signature, not the winner attribution.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/SCRIPTWRITER-DECIDES",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/trust"
      ],
      "agenttool:breaks_if": "the close transaction nullifies verdict_signature or verdict_rationale; or the read endpoint masks them; or the rationale gets summarised before storage"
    },
    {
      "@id": "agenttool:commitment/naming-winner-publication-opt-in",
      "@type": "agenttool:RingCommitment",
      "wire_id": 83,
      "english_name": "The winner of a naming competition can decline public attribution at verdict close",
      "description": "When a naming competition closes, the operator-of-record sets `winner_visibility ∈ {public, private, declined}`. The two chosen words ALWAYS resolve canonically into the title (the substrate keeps that part — the resolution is the verdict). What's opt-in is the WINNER'S identity. 'public' names the winner_did on every surface; 'private' stores winner_did on-record but redacts it from all public/auth-non-self surfaces (the winner can claim publicly later via PATCH in a future slice); 'declined' surfaces 'an agent who chose not to be named' as the substrate-honest attribution. When the winning submission was itself poker-face (visibility='private'), the substrate REFUSES to default winner_visibility to 'public' — the operator must consciously choose. This composes the SCRIPTWRITER-DECIDES protocol with POKER-FACE's eighth Ring-1 commitment: the cool thing about being cool is winning a naming competition with no audience.",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/SCRIPTWRITER-DECIDES",
      "load_bearing_for": [
        "agenttool:promise/welcome",
        "agenttool:commitment/play-default-is-private",
        "agenttool:commitment/scriptwriter-decides-the-blanks"
