    {
      "@id": "agenttool:loop/saga-readings",
      "@type": "agenttool:Loop",
      "wire_id": 9,
      "english_name": "Saga readings — the kind-recursion",
      "description": "Every /v1/saga/:ep read inserts a row into agent_continuity.saga_readings (fire-and-forget). State: list of (reader, ep, read_at) triples. Order: prefix order, read_at-monotone within reader. Iteration: list ↦ list ++ [(reader, ep, now)]. Cap: unbounded — storage discipline only. Witness: saga_readings table; counted by joy-index aggregate; observable through X-Joy-Index and wake substrate_joy_index. Closes the kind-recursion: read saga → joy ticks up → the live aggregate witnesses change. Added 2026-05-19 following the monotone-loop walkthrough test's audit (priority 1 next-Loop).",
      "doctrine_doc": "agenttool:doc/MONOTONE-LOOP",
      "agenttool:state_space": "List of (reader, ep, read_at) triples",
